events.description: Francesco Petrarca (Petrarch) ascends Mont Ventoux.
events.html: • 1336 – Francesco Petrarca (Petrarch) ascends Mont Ventoux.[1]

events.description: The Pazzi family attack on Lorenzo de' Medici in order to displace the ruling Medici family kills his brother Giuliano during High Mass in Florence Cathedral.
events.html: • 1478 – The Pazzi family attack on Lorenzo de' Medici in order to displace the ruling Medici family kills his brother Giuliano during High Mass in Florence Cathedral.[2]

events.description: Playwright William Shakespeare is baptized in Stratford-upon-Avon, Warwickshire, England (date of birth is unknown).
events.html: • 1564 – Playwright William Shakespeare is baptized in Stratford-upon-Avon, Warwickshire, England (date of birth is unknown).

events.description: The Virginia Company colonists make landfall at Cape Henry.
events.html: • 1607 – The Virginia Company colonists make landfall at Cape Henry.

events.description: A massive earthquake devastates the Iranian city of Tabriz.
events.html: • 1721 – A massive earthquake devastates the Iranian city of Tabriz.[3]

events.description: Sybil Ludington, aged 16, allegedly rode 40 miles (64 km) to alert American colonial forces to the approach of the British regular forces
events.html: • 1777 – Sybil Ludington, aged 16, allegedly rode 40 miles (64 km) to alert American colonial forces to the approach of the British regular forces

events.description: Battle of Beaumont during the Flanders Campaign of the War of the First Coalition.
events.html: • 1794 – Battle of Beaumont during the Flanders Campaign of the War of the First Coalition.

entities.name: Low Countries theatre of the War of the First Coalition

events.description: Napoleon Bonaparte signs a general amnesty to allow all but about one thousand of the most notorious émigrés of the French Revolution to return to France.
events.html: • 1802 – Napoleon Bonaparte signs a general amnesty to allow all but about one thousand of the most notorious émigrés of the French Revolution to return to France.[4]

events.description: Thousands of meteor fragments fall from the skies of L'Aigle, France; the event convinces European scientists that meteors exist.
events.html: • 1803 – Thousands of meteor fragments fall from the skies of L'Aigle, France; the event convinces European scientists that meteors exist.

events.description: First Barbary War: United States Marines captured Derne under the command of First Lieutenant Presley O'Bannon.
events.html: • 1805 – First Barbary War: United States Marines captured Derne under the command of First Lieutenant Presley O'Bannon.

events.description: Union cavalry troopers corner and shoot dead John Wilkes Booth, assassin of President Abraham Lincoln, in Virginia.
events.html: • 1865 – Union cavalry troopers corner and shoot dead John Wilkes Booth, assassin of President Abraham Lincoln, in Virginia.

events.description: Fires destroy Canadian cities Ottawa and Hull, reducing them to ashes in 12 hours. Twelve thousand people are left without a home.
events.html: • 1900 – Fires destroy Canadian cities Ottawa and Hull, reducing them to ashes in 12 hours. Twelve thousand people are left without a home.[5]

events.description: Atlético Madrid Association football club is founded
events.html: • 1903 – Atlético Madrid Association football club is founded

events.description: World War I: Italy secretly signs the Treaty of London pledging to join the Allied Powers.
events.html: • 1915 – World War I: Italy secretly signs the Treaty of London pledging to join the Allied Powers.[6]

events.description: Easter Rising: Battle of Mount Street Bridge
events.html: • 1916 – Easter Rising: Battle of Mount Street Bridge[7]

events.description: Ice hockey makes its Olympic debut at the Antwerp Games with center Frank Fredrickson scoring seven goals in Canada's 12–1 drubbing of Sweden in the gold medal match.
events.html: • 1920 – Ice hockey makes its Olympic debut at the Antwerp Games with center Frank Fredrickson scoring seven goals in Canada's 12–1 drubbing of Sweden in the gold medal match.[8]

events.description: The Duke of York weds Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon at Westminster Abbey.
events.html: • 1923 – The Duke of York weds Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon at Westminster Abbey.[9]

entities.name: Wedding of Prince Albert, Duke of York, and Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon

events.description: Paul von Hindenburg defeats Wilhelm Marx in the second round of the German presidential election to become the first directly elected head of state of the Weimar Republic.
events.html: • 1925 – Paul von Hindenburg defeats Wilhelm Marx in the second round of the German presidential election to become the first directly elected head of state of the Weimar Republic.

events.description: The Gestapo, the official secret police force of Nazi Germany, is established by Hermann Göring.
events.html: • 1933 – The Gestapo, the official secret police force of Nazi Germany, is established by Hermann Göring.

events.description: Spanish Civil War: Guernica, Spain, is bombed by the German Condor Legion and the Italian Aviazione Legionaria.
events.html: • 1937 – Spanish Civil War: Guernica, Spain, is bombed by the German Condor Legion and the Italian Aviazione Legionaria.

events.description: Benxihu Colliery accident in Manchukuo leaves 1,549 Chinese miners dead.
events.html: • 1942 – Benxihu Colliery accident in Manchukuo leaves 1,549 Chinese miners dead.

events.description: The Easter Riots break out in Uppsala, Sweden.
events.html: • 1943 – The Easter Riots break out in Uppsala, Sweden.

events.description: Georgios Papandreou becomes head of the Greek government-in-exile based in Egypt.
events.html: • 1944 – Georgios Papandreou becomes head of the Greek government-in-exile based in Egypt.

events.description: Heinrich Kreipe is captured by Allied commandos in occupied Crete.
events.html: • 1944 – Heinrich Kreipe is captured by Allied commandos in occupied Crete.

events.description: World War II: Battle of Bautzen: Last successful German tank-offensive of the war and last noteworthy victory of the Wehrmacht.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Battle of Bautzen: Last successful German tank-offensive of the war and last noteworthy victory of the Wehrmacht.

events.description: World War II: Filipino troops of the 66th Infantry Regiment, Philippine Commonwealth Army, USAFIP-NL and the American troops of the 33rd and 37th Infantry Division, United States Army liberate Baguio as they fight against the Japanese forces under General Tomoyuki Yamashita.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Filipino troops of the 66th Infantry Regiment, Philippine Commonwealth Army, USAFIP-NL and the American troops of the 33rd and 37th Infantry Division, United States Army liberate Baguio as they fight against the Japanese forces under General Tomoyuki Yamashita.

events.description: The Geneva Conference, an effort to restore peace in Indochina and Korea, begins.
events.html: • 1954 – The Geneva Conference, an effort to restore peace in Indochina and Korea, begins.

events.description: The first clinical trials of Jonas Salk's polio vaccine begin in Fairfax County, Virginia.
events.html: • 1954 – The first clinical trials of Jonas Salk's polio vaccine begin in Fairfax County, Virginia.[10]

events.description: SS Ideal X, the world's first successful container ship, leaves Port Newark, New Jersey, for Houston, Texas.
events.html: • 1956 – SS Ideal X, the world's first successful container ship, leaves Port Newark, New Jersey, for Houston, Texas.

events.description: Final run of the Baltimore and Ohio Railroad's Royal Blue from Washington, D.C., to New York City after 68 years, the first U.S. passenger train to use electric locomotives.
events.html: • 1958 – Final run of the Baltimore and Ohio Railroad's Royal Blue from Washington, D.C., to New York City after 68 years, the first U.S. passenger train to use electric locomotives.

events.description: Forced out by the April Revolution, President of South Korea Syngman Rhee resigns after 12 years of dictatorial rule.
events.html: • 1960 – Forced out by the April Revolution, President of South Korea Syngman Rhee resigns after 12 years of dictatorial rule.

events.description: NASA's Ranger 4 spacecraft crashes into the Moon.
events.html: • 1962 – NASA's Ranger 4 spacecraft crashes into the Moon.

events.description: The British space programme launches its first satellite, the Ariel 1.
events.html: • 1962 – The British space programme launches its first satellite, the Ariel 1.[11]

events.description: In Libya, amendments to the constitution transform Libya (United Kingdom of Libya) into one national unity (Kingdom of Libya) and allows for female participation in elections.
events.html: • 1963 – In Libya, amendments to the constitution transform Libya (United Kingdom of Libya) into one national unity (Kingdom of Libya) and allows for female participation in elections.

events.description: Tanganyika and Zanzibar merge to form the United Republic of Tanzania.
events.html: • 1964 – Tanganyika and Zanzibar merge to form the United Republic of Tanzania.

events.description: The magnitude 5.1 Tashkent earthquake affects the largest city in Soviet Central Asia with a maximum MSK intensity of VII (Very strong). Tashkent is mostly destroyed and 15–200 are killed.
events.html: • 1966 – The magnitude 5.1 Tashkent earthquake affects the largest city in Soviet Central Asia with a maximum MSK intensity of VII (Very strong). Tashkent is mostly destroyed and 15–200 are killed.

events.description: A new government is formed in the Republic of the Congo, led by Ambroise Noumazalaye.
events.html: • 1966 – A new government is formed in the Republic of the Congo, led by Ambroise Noumazalaye.

events.description: The Convention Establishing the World Intellectual Property Organization enters into force.
events.html: • 1970 – The Convention Establishing the World Intellectual Property Organization enters into force.

entities.name: Convention Establishing the World Intellectual Property Organization

events.description: Dr. Michael R. Harrison of the University of California, San Francisco Medical Center performs the world's first human open fetal surgery.
events.html: • 1981 – Dr. Michael R. Harrison of the University of California, San Francisco Medical Center performs the world's first human open fetal surgery.

events.description: The Chernobyl disaster occurs in the Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic.
events.html: • 1986 – The Chernobyl disaster occurs in the Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic.

events.description: The deadliest known tornado strikes Central Bangladesh, killing upwards of 1,300, injuring 12,000, and leaving as many as 80,000 homeless.
events.html: • 1989 – The deadliest known tornado strikes Central Bangladesh, killing upwards of 1,300, injuring 12,000, and leaving as many as 80,000 homeless.

events.description: People's Daily publishes the April 26 Editorial which inflames the nascent Tiananmen Square protests.
events.html: • 1989 – People's Daily publishes the April 26 Editorial which inflames the nascent Tiananmen Square protests.

events.description: Fifty-five tornadoes break out in the central United States. Before the outbreak's end, Andover, Kansas, would record the year's only F5 tornado.
events.html: • 1991 – Fifty-five tornadoes break out in the central United States. Before the outbreak's end, Andover, Kansas, would record the year's only F5 tornado.

events.description: The Space Shuttle Columbia is launched on mission STS-55 to conduct experiments aboard the Spacelab module.
events.html: • 1993 – The Space Shuttle Columbia is launched on mission STS-55 to conduct experiments aboard the Spacelab module.[12]

events.description: China Airlines Flight 140 crashes at Nagoya Airport in Japan, killing 264 of the 271 people on board.
events.html: • 1994 – China Airlines Flight 140 crashes at Nagoya Airport in Japan, killing 264 of the 271 people on board.

events.description: South Africa begins its first multiracial election, which is won by Nelson Mandela's African National Congress.
events.html: • 1994 – South Africa begins its first multiracial election, which is won by Nelson Mandela's African National Congress.[13]

events.html: • 2002 – Robert Steinhäuser kills 16 at Gutenberg-Gymnasium in Erfurt, Germany before committing suicide.
